Install the package xmlto, which will pull in the other dependencies you need to work with docbook.

To generate the html, go to the trunk and run:
make html

Use blufish to help you to write the docbook xml.

Using CSS with docbook:
http://www.sagehill.net/docbookxsl/UsingCSS.html

Reference:
http://www.docbook.org/tdg/en/html/part2.html
http://www.sagehill.net/docbookxsl/index.html